  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: 1.4.0-unstable\nOS & Version: OSX \nCommit hash : f93758bf64ea6d8720ceccca4c6b183d25cda30d\n#### Expected behaviour\n\n`eth_estimateGas` should return exactly the amount of gas that the execution would take.\n#### Actual behaviour\n\n`eth_estimateGas` returns the value of the parameter gas when the execution would fail.\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nOne example is estimating gas of the now closed digix crowd sale contract: \n\n```\ncurl -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_estimateGas\",\"params\":[{\"to\":\"0xf0160428a8552ac9bb7e050d90eeade4ddd52843\",\"value\":\"0xff22\",\"gasPrice\":\"0x051da038cc\",\"gas\":\"0xffffff\"}],\"id\":1}' http://localhost:8545\n-> {\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":\"0xffffff\"}\n```\n\nGeth says a transaction would use several millions of gas for its execution.\n\nHowever, an actual transaction only uses 121,000 gas because the execution fails: http://etherscan.io/tx/0xf0512cb94a5c04643cbc846f70e7308f6e81c44097da61a42a4b9b86f3565fda\n\nGas estimates should be correct, whether the execution succeeds or fails.\n",
