    "body": "Cheers. Yes I've I can confirm this issue. I've also figured what the problem is. \n\nThe value returned to estimate the gas is the same value returned that figures out the exact amount of gas used, however, the gas used may not always be the amount of gas required. The gas used amount is the normalised value which includes suicides and storage clearings.\n\nIn order to fix this issue we need to patch up the `core.ApplyMessage` the return not only the gas used but also the actual amount it needed to run the entire transition **without** the reductions. \n",
